1959a: 316. Types Mus. Zool. Univ. Sao Paulo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="231">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33999" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole sensitiva Borgmeier" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensitiva">sensitiva</taxonomicName>
, possibly referring to the sensory function of the long body hairs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="231">
diagnosis A small, light reddish brown member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142247" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Atta diligens Smith" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diligens">diligens</taxonomicName>
group with moderately abundant to dense, very long, erect to semierect, often strongly curved hairs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="231">Major: sculpturing of head consists entirely of carinulae, which are limited to the anterior third of the head capsule and absent from the frontal lobes; promesonotal profde 3-lobed; pronotal humerus rounded in dorsal-oblique view; pilosity of gaster shorter and much denser than on the rest of the body. Minor: humerus rounded and pronotum smooth and shiny.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="231">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181681" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole longiseta Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiseta">longiseta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33945" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pubiventris Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubiventris">pubiventris</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181704" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole variegata Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">variegata</taxonomicName>
, differing in many details of body form and sculpturing, as shown. See also 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33625" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole blumenauensis Kempf" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blumenauensis">blumenauensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181680" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rochai Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochai">rochai</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33996" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole seeldrayersi Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seeldrayersi">seeldrayersi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34079" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole vafra Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafra">vafra</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="231">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.94, HL 0.94, SL 0.64, EL 0.16, PW 0.48. Paratype minor: HW 0.58, HL 0.64, SL 0.76, EL 0.14, PW 0.38.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="231">Color Major: light reddish brown; gaster a shade darker; appendages yellowish brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="231">Minor: light brown, gaster a shade darker and appendages a shade lighter than head and mesosoma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="231">Range Known from the type series from Rio de Janeiro, a series from near San Juan de Arama, Meta, Colombia, and, according to Longino (1997), the Atlantic and Pacific slopes of Costa Rica to 700 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="231">Biology In Costa Rica, Longino (1997) found the species in litter and recruiting to baits on the floor of rainforests.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
